cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

This paper is about semantic segmentation, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, it is most likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel module for calculating and combining class centers, which involves some level of machine learning. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves some natural language processing (NLP) in terms of describing the proposed method, which could place it in the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the paper does not involve any hardware or systems design, so it is unlikely to belong to the cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) or cs.OS (Operating Systems) sub-categories.
